items.title: Pollock starts anew after breaking out of slump
items.summary: The results weren't there for outfielder A.J. Pollock, but D-backs manager Torey Lovullo was convinced that a breakout was near.
items.content: The results weren't there for outfielder A.J. Pollock, but D-backs manager Torey Lovullo was convinced that a breakout was near.

items.title: Behind Taylor's rise: a new, dynamic swing
items.summary: When the Dodgers finally steer their ship out of the rocks and hit dry land come October -- and they will make the playoffs, despite this month's dramatics -- it's difficult to imagine them making much noise without Chris Taylor. Their high-socked, higher-energy leadoff hitter ambushed the lineup in April and nose-dove into so many rallies since, it's worth considering the reality of an autumn ago.
